args:
When morning comes, Alfie wakes to find Nevin
and Ramiel there beside him. Seeing that they
protected him all night makes him think it might
be okay to trust them, especially when Nevin
promises to keep him and his mother safe.
I know. It's faint, but I can feel it.\nIt's...Meene's.
So that's the key to perdition!
By the authority of the Goddess, entrusted\nto me in this key, I command the gates of\ntruth to open.
I'm all right... Just...please. Take it.
It's really one of the Scrolls of Perdition...
Yeah, I read it. Let's get back to the inn.
As soon as I felt Meene's mana, I realized\nthat I need to make something. I should\nhave it put together by morning.
What happened? I was tired because\nthe cold made me sleepy, and then...
Not like we could've made it back to town\nthrough that blizzard even if we wanted to.
He just means we're both glad to see you\nawake and feeling well.
But why help me? Aren't you our enemies?
We have no intention of harming you\nor your mother, Alf.
True. And if I'm honest, before we met you,\nI was ready to take it by force.
But after talking with you and learning how\nyou felt, that idea got tabled quick.
I couldn't stand to see MY parent get hurt,\nso I get exactly what you're feeling.
So what are you gonna do?
I can't imagine anyone would stumble\nupon us out here by pure coincidence.
Which means it's an enemy\neither ours or Alfie's.
Alfie? Stay behind me. I'll keep you safe,\nno matter what.
You kept your mom safe all this time,\nwhich makes you worth protecting.
And I promise to protect both you\nAND your mom if you'll let me.
You'd really make a promise like that\nto someone like me?
Not someone LIKE you. Just you.
